---
id: Creating-and-editing-articles-in-Github
title: How to Create and edit articles in Github
sidebar_label: Style Guide
---

To create a new article you should navigate to the desired parent folder in which you want to create it.
Clicking on New file will open your new article.

Image


You should add a header section at the top of the page that should have an id (has to be the same name as file), the document title and a side bar label.

---
id: name of file
title: Document title
sidebar_label: Text that will appear in sidebar
---


Headers and sub headers should be used for better text format. You can follow our style guide to see all different options.


After making your changes you should commit your file and start a pull request so our team can review it.

image


After your file approval it should show in the public site within minutes



